# CODEOWNERS — risk-tier merge gate
#
# Paths listed here are meant to require @ckrhehfl's review before merge,
# via branch protection's "Require review from Code Owners" on main. In
# practice, verified empirically: GitHub does not enforce this when the PR
# author is also the sole code owner (self-approval is blocked, but the
# review requirement is simply not raised at all rather than blocking) —
# it does not hold up as a hard server-side gate for a solo-author repo
# until PRs are opened by an identity distinct from @ckrhehfl (bot/app).
# Until then this file plus this comment is the documented boundary that
# @ckrhehfl / any agent operating this repo must treat as a manual-review
# requirement even though GitHub won't enforce it technically. See CLAUDE.md
# "Branch and Merge / Auto-merge Policy" for the full explanation.
#
# Anything NOT matched below has no required reviewer: CI + CodeRabbit
# passing is sufficient for auto-merge. Keep this file's boundaries in sync
# with .coderabbit.yaml's path_instructions — same risk classification.

# Java Trading Plane: OMS / Risk Gateway / Execution / ExchangeAdapter /
# Reconciliation / Kill Switch — all execution and risk-affecting code.
/java/               @ckrhehfl

# Shared Python/Java contract schemas — breaking changes ripple into the
# Java trading plane.
/schemas/             @ckrhehfl

# Runtime config: leverage, risk/loss limits, live-trading flags.
/configs/             @ckrhehfl

# CI/CD workflows — modifying these is equivalent to code execution with
# repo secrets; a classic supply-chain attack surface.
/.github/             @ckrhehfl

# Governance/policy files themselves.
/CLAUDE.md            @ckrhehfl
/.coderabbit.yaml     @ckrhehfl
